True, you are what you eat, but more accurately &#39;you are what you absorb&#39; 

Nuts that pass right through you (I know you&#39;ve seen them) are as nutritious to your body as the nuts you didn&#39;t eat.  Your body must absorb the food in order for you to use the nutrients. 

Foods high in fiber might not get absorbed, however they often act as scrubbers for the insides of your digestive system where things can easily get embedded and cause problems.
